                  <b>A thought for today<br>
                  </b>Nature is ever at work building and pulling down,
creating=20
                  and destroying, keeping everything whirling and
flowing, allowing=20
                  no rest but in rhythmical motion, chasing everything in
endless=20
                  song out of one beautiful form into another - John
MUIR, Naturalist=20
                  and explorer (1838-1914)<br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <b>And another one<br>
                  </b>Patriotism is proud of a country's virtues and
eager to=20
                  correct its deficiencies; it also acknowledges the
legitimate=20
                  patriotism of other countries, with their own specific
virtues.=20
                  The pride of nationalism, however, trumpets its
country's virtues=20
                  and denies its deficiencies, while it is contemptuous
toward=20
                  the virtues of other countries. It wants to be, and
proclaims=20
                  itself to be, &quot;the greatest&quot;, but greatness
is not=20
                  required of a country; only goodness is - Sydney J.
HARRIS,=20
                  journalist and author (1917-1986)<br>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <b>And a third one<br>
                  </b>The difference in mind between man and the higher
animals,=20
                  great as it is, certainly is one of degree and not of
kind -=20
                  Charles DARWIN, naturalist and author (1809-1882)<br>
