            <br>
            <b>PhD studentship =96 Site Specific Land Management based on
Proximal=20
            Soil Sensing<br>
            </b>- Academic Supervisors: Dr Abdul Mouazen<br>
            - Co-supervisor: Dr Roland Corstanje<br>
            - Duration: Three years<br>
            - Start Date: ASAP<br>
            - Contact: Dr Abdul MOUAZEN (E-mail:
a.mouazen(a)cranfield.ac.uk)<br>
            <br>
            &gt; Supported by the Douglas Bomford Trust and HGCA, a
studentship=20
            up to =A312,500 p.a. for 3 years plus fees is available<br>
            <br>
            &gt; The project proposes to build a sensor fusion platform
that gathers=20
            a Vis-NIR sensor together with electromagnetic induction
(EMI) and=20
            capacitance sensors. Data output from these two proximal
sensing systems=20
            will be combined with data obtained on topography, crop,
weather and=20
            yield. Using advanced geo-statistical analysis, management
zones of=20
            soil and crop will be delineated and utilised for site
specific management=20
            of tillage and fertilisation, including organic and inorganic
fertilisers.<br>
            See:
<a href=3D"http://www.cranfield.ac.uk/sas/aboutus/staff/mouazena.jsp">http:=
//www.cranfield.ac.uk/sas/aboutus/staff/mouazena.jsp</a><br>
            Contact : Abdul Mounem MOUAZEN<br>
            E-mail: a.mouazen(a)cranfield.ac.uk<br>
