            &gt; Conference Focus<br>
            E-Agriculture has a crucial role in the empowerment of
farmers in=20
            rural areas all over the world though information and
communication=20
            processes, supporting them so they can improve the quality of
life=20
            for themselves and for their families. The technological
interventions=20
            can raise the living standards in marginalized communities by
leveraging=20
            agricultural output and improvement of through technological
interventions.=20
            ICT technologies give access to timely information such as
weather=20
            forecasts, better pricing and allow the facilitating on-line
trading=20
            which can improve the productivity of rural agricultural
activities.<br>
            <br>
            Furthermore, the deployment of ICT can provide a framework
for monitoring=20
            of the use and efficient allocation/exploitation of natural
resources=20
            as well as the support for remote diagnosis and treatment of
diseases,=20
            providing a valuable tool for the improvement of the quality
of Life.<br>
            <br>
            The two day conference will focus on for the
conceptualization, design,=20
            development, evaluation and application of innovative ways to
use=20
            Information and Communication Technologies in the rural
domain. The=20
            conference will, among others, explore the environmental
impact of=20
            E-Agriculture in the improvement and more efficient use of
natural=20
            resources and exploitation of nature's potential towards a
sustainable=20
            growth that best matches Africa's needs. In this course,
current trends=20
            in the fields of Agroecology and Organic Agriculture and the
way these=20
            can be supported through e-Agriculture, as well as particular
applications=20
            and use cases that meet the needs of the African continent
will be=20
            presented and discussed. In parallel, impact that the use of
e-services=20
            can have in the field of Food, Earth and Life sciences,
taking into=20
            account the particularities of Africa, will be
evaluated.<br>
            <br>
            The conference will bring together scientists, government
agencies,=20
            technology developers, engineers and NGO in an attempt to
create a=20
            platform to exchange ideas and best practices on the
implementation=20
            of e-Services for Agriculture, Food, Environment and Life
sciences,=20
            with emphasis on e-Agriculture initiatives worldwide.<br>
            <br>
            The event will include plenary sessions with distinguished
keynote=20
            presentations and panel discussions with leading experts on
cross-domain=20
            issues. In the context of the event, participants will be
offered=20
            the choice to participate in interesting presentations and
discussions.<br>
            <br>
            e-AFRICA is looking for scientific papers to be submitted in
the following=20
            areas:<br>
            <br>
            - ICT and Organic Agriculture/Agroecology<br>
            - On-line trading of agricultural products<br>
            - Supporting agricultural education/training through=20
ICT<br>
            - Raising awareness on environmental issues through the use
of web=20
            technologies<br>
            - Monitoring and decision support systems for environmental
protection<br>
            - ICT support for earth sciences<br>
            - Improving quality of life in rural areas through ICT<br>
            - Robotics and automation systems in agriculture and
environmental=20
            protection<br>
            - Web and mobile services for environmental/agricultural
issues<br>
            - Enhancing chain management and traceability in agriculture
chain=20
            through novel technologies<br>
            - ICT adoption in Africa<br>
            See:
<a href=3D"http://eafricaconference.org/">http://eafricaconference.org</a><=
br>
